# Smart Home Architecture v1.0

## System Overview
Two-node distributed IoT system for climate and lighting control.

![System Diagram](diagram.jpg)

## Components

### Living Room (Master Node)
- **Controller:** NodeMCU ESP8266
- **Sensors:** DHT22 (temperature, humidity)
- **Actuators:** Light, Fan (2-channel relay)
- **Display:** OLED 0.96" (local status)
- **Communication:** WiFi AP, HTTP server

### Bedroom (Slave Node)
- **Controller:** NodeMCU ESP8266
- **Sensors:** DHT22, PIR motion
- **Actuators:** AC unit (1-channel relay)
- **Communication:** WiFi STA, reports to Master

### Mobile Interface
- **App:** HTTP Request Shortcuts
- **Controls:** Light, Fan, AC, Display, Motion status
- **Protocol:** HTTP GET over 2.4GHz WiFi

## Data Flow
1. User taps shortcut on phone
2. HTTP request to Living Room NodeMCU
3. NodeMCU toggles relay / updates OLED
4. (Future) Bedroom node reports to Living Room via ESP-NOW
5. (Future) Data logged to SD card

## Future Extensions
- [ ] MQTT broker for cloud integration
- [ ] Voice control (Google Assistant)
- [ ] Mobile app with MIT App Inventor
- [ ] OTA firmware updates
